931+oldest&hl=en&sa=X&ei=0DxoUcqOKfSi4AO8p4GYDg&ved=0CDEQ6AEwAA |author=Carolyn Farquhar Ulrich |title=Ulrich's International Periodicals Directory |publisher= Bowker|date=1987 |accessdate=April 12, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CiUoAQAAIAAJ&q=%22Jewish+Standard%22+1931+oldest&dq=%22Jewish+Standard%22+1931+oldest&hl=en&sa=X&ei=0DxoUcqOKfSi4AO8p4GYDg&ved=0CFAQ6AEwBw |title=The Joseph Jacobs directory of the Jewish press in America |author=Joseph Jacobs Organization |publisher= |date=1972 |accessdate=April 12, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GydaAAAAYAAJ&q=%22Jewish+Standard%22+1931+oldest&dq=%22Jewish+Standard%22+1931+oldest&hl=en&sa=X&ei=0DxoUcqOKfSi4AO8p4GYDg&ved=0CGUQ6AEwCw |author= |title=Ethnic directory of New Jersey |publisher= W. H. Wise|date=1978|accessdate=April 12, 2013}}</ref> It has partnered with the online newspaper ''[[Times of Israel]]'' and is hosted by the latter's website platform.
Unaffiliated with any program, organization, or movement, it states it is dedicated to giving expression to all phases of Jewish life. The ''Jewish Standard'' is independently owned, and says it is committed to "Jewish continuity and to Israel and America's well-being that have made both countries blessed."<ref name="jstandard1">{{cite web|url=http://www.jstandard.com/content/item/about_us |title=About Us |publisher=The Jewish Standard |date= |accessdate=April 12, 2013}}</ref>
==Expansion== In 1984, the company took over publishing of the ''Jewish Community News'', the Jewish newspaper of [[Passaic County, New Jersey|Passaic County]].<ref name="jstandard1"/> In 1991, the company began publishing the ''Rockland Jewish Reporter'' as the official publication of The Jewish Federation of Rockland County.<ref name="jstandard1"/> In 2002, the company began publishing ''About Our Children'', a source for information for Jewish families.<ref name="jstandard1"/>
The papers have won numerous awards from the [[American Jewish Press Association]], the North Jersey Press Club, the [[Society of Professional Journalists]] and from Parenting Publications of America.<ref name="jstandard1"/>
